    },
    {
      "text": "Medabots: Metabee and Medabots: Rokusho (メダロット弐CORE クワガタバージョン・カブトバージョン, Medarotto Ni CORE Kabuto Bājon · Kuwagata Bājon) is a set of two 2D top-down role-playing video games in the Medabots series, developed by Natsume Co., Ltd. for Game Boy Advance. It is a remake of the Japan-exclusive title Medarot 2 (メダロット２, Medarotto 2), which was released for the Game Boy Color in 1999. It was later re-released on the Wii U Virtual Console on October 1, 2015 in Europe, on December 10, 2015 for North America, and on January 27, 2016 in Japan.\nMedabots is one of only three games in the series to be released outside Japan, the other two being Medabots AX and Medabots Infinity.",
